<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS -
        Installation - Lower Crankcase
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.3.6" svcproctype="torque" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Lower Crankcase</title>
        <para>With acceptable bearing clearance, install the lower crankcase as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new lower crankcase seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to lower bearing inserts, crankshaft journals, and lower crankcase
                bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650808" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD07/D0756.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Main bearing bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inboard main bearing cap bolts (M14 x 127) (10)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outboard main bearing cap bolts (M14 x 114) (10)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure that the longer main cap bolts (M14 x 127) are installed
                    inboard and the shorter bolts (M14 x 114) are installed outboard.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650839.1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0754.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"
                     box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque sequence for main bearing mounting bolts to lower crankcase</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 10 inboard main bearing cap bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 10 outboard main bearing cap bolts.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Initially torque bolts to 122 N&#183;m (90 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Increase torque for bolts to 163 N&#183;m (120 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Finally, torque bolts to 231 N&#183;m (170 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650839" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0728.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"
                     box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque sequence for outer lower crankcase bolts - 2004 Model year</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For 2004 Model Year, install eight M8 x 30 bolts around outside of lower crankcase and torque in
                    sequence to 31 N&#183;m (23 lbf&#183;ft).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Confirm that gear backlash between camshaft and crankshaft is within specifications.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650841" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd03/d0304.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Gear backlash check (camshaft gear to crankshaft gear)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check camshaft gear to crankshaft gear backlash as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on rear of engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position dial indicator tip on a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate gear by hand and read indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If backlash exceeds specified limits , replace camshaft gear.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650842" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0713.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>End play check for crankshaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft flange</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check crankshaft end play as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Mount dial indicator on crankcase with indicator tip on the end of crankshaft flange as
                    shown.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft forward with pry bar and zero the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pry crankshaft back and forth while reading dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
